@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place 'Eqwi' where you
want on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files
or Libraries are needed. However, your Workbench must have at least
8 colours.

                             How to play?

  Each game board includes 2 corridors of varying lengths that
start from the center and 'snake' their way up to dead ends that
are located next to both left and right edges in the game board. At
the start of a game, a number of tiles are placed from the center
space in both corridors.

  Playing the game is pretty simple: click on any position in a
corridor that is either empty or already occupied by a tile, except
on the last tile of a series of tiles. The lowermost tile (the next
tile) of the 3 tiles that are shown at the right of the game board
will be placed at the end of a series of tiles in the corresponding
corridor.

  If you click on the last tile of a series of tiles, that last
tile will be 'exchanged' with the next tile... however, if both
tiles are of the same type, in that case the next tile will go
right next to the clicked tile. The only tile that cannot be moved
or exchanged this way is the center tile.

  As you place 3 tiles of the same type, one following the other,
they are then removed from the game board and you get 1 point. When
you succeed in emptying an entire corridor, including the center
tile; the remaining tiles of the other corridor, if there are any,
will also be removed and you will get additional points according
to the number of empty spaces that remained in that other corridor
before the tiles were removed...

  Avoid as much as possible to completely fill up a corridor,
because a tile placed in the last space, or dead-end space, will
blow up and that would end the game... unless, of course, if that
tile is of the same type as of the 2 preceding tiles in that
corridor, as this would remove those 3 tiles.

  Have fun!

@endnode

